CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 21, 1962, page A13, reads: "The Debonnaires - This non-profit organization has contributed to worthy charitable organizations since it was formed. The Debonnaires sent Ronald Howard to camp for two weeks in 1960. Last year, the members donated linens to the Aged Ministers and Laymen's home, on Oakwood St., and this year the club sponsored a Shamrock Ball, from which proceeds will be used to purchase a life membership in NAACP. Here Justine Allen, president of the Debonnaires, presents a check as a payment on the life membership, to Lu Davenport, while Emma Mosby, Nadine Mosby, Marguerite Mosby, Agnes Reynolds and Elouise Morris look on. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Six women and a man, members of the Debonnaires, left to right: Emma Mosby, Lu Davenport, Nadine Mosby, Marguerite Mosby, Justine Allen, holding a check, Agnes Reynolds, and Elouise Morris, standing in interior with light colored walls and doors, another version
